     "text": [
      "1. **Confirm whether two Prefect tasks/flows are hitting the same SQLite file at the same time**\n",
      "   - Check recent flow runs, retries, and any parallel task execution.\n",
      "   - Look for overlapping jobs that read/write the same local SQLite DB used for Bronze/Silver/Gold orchestration or state tracking.\n",
      "   - **Most likely fix first:** this error is most often caused by concurrent access to SQLite.\n",
      "\n",
      "2. **Identify the exact SQLite database file in use**\n",
      "   - Inspect the config/env vars for the pipeline to find the path to the `.sqlite`, `.db`, or Prefect local metadata DB.\n",
      "   - Verify whether that file sits on a network mount, shared volume, or temp directory that multiple workers can touch.\n",
      "\n",
      "3. **Check for a stuck process holding the SQLite lock**\n",
      "   - On the host/container running the flow, inspect running Prefect workers, Python processes, or any scheduled job still active.\n",
      "   - If a prior run crashed mid-write, it may have left the DB locked until the process exits or is terminated.\n",
      "\n",
      "4. **Look for long-running transactions or uncommitted writes in the code path**\n",
      "   - Focus on steps just before the failure: Bronze staging write, Silver gate persistence, or atomic swap bookkeeping for open periods.\n",
      "   - Verify every SQLite write closes the connection and commits promptly.\n",
      "   - Avoid holding a connection open across network I/O, Soda checks, or Snowflake calls.\n",
      "\n",
      "5. **If the pipeline runs in parallel, temporarily force serial execution**\n",
      "   - Reduce Prefect concurrency for the affected flow/task group.\n",
      "   - Disable concurrent retries or overlapping schedule windows for the same period.\n",
      "   - This is a quick validation that the issue is lock contention rather than corruption.\n",
      "\n",
      "6. **Check whether the failing step is doing an atomic swap for an open period**\n",
      "   - Open periods use atomic swap, which can require multiple write operations.\n",
      "   - Make sure the swap logic is not running twice for the same accounting period.\n",
      "   - Verify the lock isn’t being held while the pipeline waits on external validation.\n",
      "\n",
      "7. **Review SQLite-specific settings**\n",
      "   - If possible, enable WAL mode and a reasonable timeout for writes.\n",
      "   - Confirm the code uses a busy timeout rather than failing immediately on contention.\n",
      "   - If this is already set, increase the timeout briefly to see if the lock is only transient.\n",
      "\n",
      "8. **Make sure SQLite is not being used as a shared production concurrency layer**\n",
      "   - SQLite is fragile for multi-process production orchestration if many workers write to it.\n",
      "   - If this DB is used for shared state, migrate that state to a server-backed store or restrict writes to a single worker.\n",
      "\n",
      "9. **Check for file permission or filesystem issues that mimic lock problems**\n",
      "   - Confirm the worker has consistent read/write access.\n",
      "   - Verify the DB file and directory are not on a flaky network filesystem or read-only mount.\n",
      "\n",
      "10. **Re-run the affected period after clearing the lock**\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "load_dotenv()\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.pipeline_flow import _get_ai_troubleshooting\n",
    "print(_get_ai_troubleshooting(\n",
    "    \"sqlite3.OperationalError: database is locked\",\n",
    "    \"Traceback (most recent call last):\\n  ...\\nsqlite3.OperationalError: database is locked\"\n",
    "))"
   ]
